cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CE

The paper deals with optimizing the meetup location of multiple moving objects along road networks, which involves spatial optimization and geoprocessing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GR (Computer Graphics), which deals with spatial data and optimization. The paper also involves heuristic methods and optimization models, which are common in the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with social activity needs and social quality of life, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves traffic conditions and minimizing costs, which are relevant to the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
